reviews.review_text: Good Show Had a great time at this show. Not bad audience recording. Bobby came to work this night.

damn nice awesome Iko>BIODTL opener, nice Althea, and great Box of Rain...
PITB>Franklin's (very good version)>Miracle>PITB jam is definitely worth the download...
solid '86 show

fun show great music and cant remember which was better between this and providence a few nights later but do remember a huge fake gorilla on top of some building above one of the parking lots we all noticed at the same time and howled.... dear mr fantasy was the high point of set II...

no kidding bob came to work... only 5 jerry tunes all night! (6 w encore)

whats with the second set?  Only Franklins (and Wheel, which isnt really a Jerry tune)

Ever seen a show with so few Garcia tunes?
step in shit 2nd set love this 2nd set... song transitions? hahha new songs just appear from nowhere... and the playin jam before drums flirts with supplication in a sweet way

nice show to be at true

hear it!

First show Pulled it up mostly for nostalgia- I knew only the material on skeletons on the closet when I showed up.  It was a beautiful spring day in Portland.  The scene blew me away all day, and then the boys at night.

Its a pretty good show when its all said and done.
snow??? I remember walking out of the show and snow on the ground......great show...

GREAT SHOW AND AUDIENCE TAPE 2nd is just fantastic 
They just keep groovin' and jammin' endlessly.

THANK YOU FOR A REAL GOOD TIME

It was 26 years ago today... that I got to hear my  first ever Box of Rain live.
(((((Thank you Phil))) It was a very sweet moment. This  show has other  great high lights, super fun opener as well as the rest of the first set the continued PITB through out the second set, a KILLER Dear Mr. Fantasy and a poetic Baby Blue encore.

A gem This is another hot show in the state of Maine... They sure like Playing here. Maybe it's the seafood they look forward to. 
 Really though for some reason they seem to rip off some true Gems in the state of Maine , Augusta in 84 , here in Portland In 82 break out of Ashes ashes as we called it then & 85 with the Day Tripper show. Outside with Lewiston in 80 and my not so favorite year of 88 but still hot smoking shows every time they come to Maine.
 About this show and the sound of this recording it is top notvh. Any 2nd set that starts with Playing in the Band is a favorite of mine because it can go anywhere. Playing in the Band Is there Dark star of the 80's
